  We present a universal concept for the Value of Information (VoI) based on
Claude Shannon's information and work of Ruslan Stratonovich that has desirable
properties for Bayesian decision theory and demand analysis. The
Shannon/Stratonovich VoI concept is compared to the concept of Hartley VoI and
applied to an epitome economic application of a circular setting generalizing
an example of Ruslan Stratonovich and allowing for a network structure and an
investigation of various economic transport costs.
